                "description": {
                    "description_data": [
                        {
                            "lang": "en",
                            "value": "An out-of-bounds memory write flaw was found in the Linux kernel\u2019s Kid-friendly Wired Controller driver. This flaw allows a local user to crash or potentially escalate their privileges on the system. It is in bigben_probe of drivers/hid/hid-bigbenff.c. The reason is incorrect assumption - bigben devices all have inputs. However, malicious devices can break this assumption, leaking to out-of-bound write."
                        }
                    ]
